-- Vestel in Turkey Falls to Month-Low on Reporting Loss in 2011
-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 2012-04-11T15:57:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-11/vestel-in-turkey-falls-to-month-low-on-reporting-loss-in-2011.html
Vestel Elektronik Sanayi & Ticaret
AS (VESTL) , a Turkish consumer electronics and home appliances
manufacturer, dropped to the lowest level in almost a month
after reporting a loss in 2011.  Vestel Elektronik fell as much as 3.6 percent before paring
its loss to 0.5 percent at 2.19 liras, the lowest since March
16.  The full-year loss was 35.4 million liras ($20 million)
last year, compared with a profit of 38.4 million liras in 2010,
Vestel said in a statement to the Istanbul Stock Exchange late
yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
